wikipedia_page.main: Frania Gillen-Buchert (born 13 November 1981) is a South African born, Scottish female former squash player. She made her international debut in 2000 and achieved her career best ranking of 53 in 2003.  Buchert graduated at the University of Stirling.Buchert competed at the Commonwealth Games in 2006, 2010 and 2014 representing Scotland. After the 2014 Commonwealth Games, she decided to retire from international squash competitions which also ended her 17 year career.
